comments.text: Over 20. 5 runs. Bowler: Soumya Sarkar. Pakistan: 5-142(rr 7.10)

Soumya Sarkar to Mohammad Rizwan. Off cutter length ball, outside off stump on the front foot Slog, mis-timed in the air uncontrolled to deep mid wicket for 2 runs, dropped catch by Ali. Two to win and Mithun is under a skier to keep the game alive. He shells it and Pakistan limp over the line. Shoaib Malik anchored the chase with 58 not out and he ensured that the home team were never under too much pressure in the runchase despite it going down to the last over. It's a very short turnaround in this series. Please join us again tomorrow for the second game. Bangladesh will be even more competitive with this workout under their belts.
